urlText: Services may be busy due to a major event
content:
Due to the NSW Premier’s Gala Concerts and Seniors Festival Expo at the International Convention Centre (ICC) Sydney, the L1 Dulwich Hill Line is expected to be busy on Thursday 13 and Friday 14 February.

On both days, extra direct light rail services will be running between Central Grand Concourse and Exhibition Centre for event attendees.

Allow plenty of extra time and plan ahead, including consider alternative transport such as walking between Central Grand Concourse and the following stops:
  • Capitol Square = approx. 6 min walk
  • Paddy’s Markets = approx. 11 min walk
  • Exhibition Centre = approx. 14 min walk
  • Convention = approx. 21 min walk
  • Pyrmont Bay = approx. 27 min walk
  • The Star = approx. 30 min walk
Visit Getting to Events for more information.
subtitle: Services may be busy due to a major event
